### Describe the Bug

i want to track redirects in my url.

i have a filepath named `src/app/[guide]/page.tsx` in next.js 14 that looks like:

```tsx
"use client"

import { notFound, redirect, useParams } from "next/navigation"

const Guide = () => {
	const { guide } = useParams()

	const guides = [
		{
			source: "/google",
			destination:
				"https://google.com/",
		},
	]

	const result = guides.find((g) => {
		const param = g.source.split("/")[1]
		if (guide === param) {
			return g
		}
	})

	if (!result) {
		return notFound()
	}

	redirect(result.destination)
}

export default Guide
```

if anyone visits `https://example.com/google`, then it should redirect to `google.com` but doesn't get tracked.

i tested it by adding a bit of timeout & it gets tracked. i've tested it & only from 1.5 seconds, it starts working. but i've made the delay to be `2` because i think it depends on loading the script & that depends on network a particular user is using. idk if i can track it like url shorteners do but that's what i want.

**current solution that works:**

```tsx
"use client"

import { notFound, redirect, useParams } from "next/navigation"
import React from "react"

const delay = 2

const Guide = () => {
	const { guide } = useParams()
	const [show, setShow] = React.useState(true)

	React.useEffect(() => {
		let timer1 = setTimeout(() => setShow(false), delay * 1000)

		return () => {
			clearTimeout(timer1)
		}
	}, [])
	
	const guides = [
		{
			source: "/google",
			destination:
				"https://google.com/",
		},
	]

	const result = guides.find((g) => {
		const param = g.source.split("/")[1]
		if (guide === param) {
			return g
		}
	})

	if (!result) {
		return notFound()
	}

	if (show) {
		return <p className="m-2">Wait, redirecting...</p>
	}

	redirect(result.destination)
}

export default Guide
```

is there a way to track redirects in umami directly without adding timeout?

maybe like https://www.zachgollwitzer.com/posts/fathom-analytics-nextjs13-app-directory

